      },
      "date": "2015-01-05 20:11:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nGot bite by the lack of PDE() on SLES11SP3. I ran across this as well. I was working on a new patch as well but its quite bit so its a good idea to break it.\nAlso params_tree.h can go away completely :-)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5fa604cdb6ae9d997d8021c7cf67b30cca0d5147",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-05 20:48:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI believe it's PDE_DATA() that's missing on SLES. This patch reduces the use of PDE().\n\nYes. It can go away. I'd rather we use smaller patches than larger ones though. One thing that's needed is to ensure that LPROCFS goes away and/or is handled sensibly.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
